THE WEEKEND OFF.

15:02.684 --> 15:04.555
-I GOT RECRUITED PLAYIN'
THE BREAKOUT TOURNAMENT.

15:07.515 --> 15:09.430
-SINCE WHEN DO YOU
PLAY ROLLER HOCKEY?

15:09.560 --> 15:11.301
-I'VE PLAYED ICE
HOCKEY ALL MY LIFE.

15:11.432 --> 15:13.260
THERE'S NOT MUCH DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN SKATES AND BLADES,

15:13.390 --> 15:15.175
IT'S BASICALLY THE SAME GAME.

15:15.305 --> 15:17.177
-WELL, YOU SHOULD'VE
CHECKED WITH ME FIRST.

15:17.829 --> 15:19.440
-I DIDN'T KNOW
I NEEDED YOUR PERMISSION.

15:21.311 --> 15:23.618
LOOK, STEPH, I HAVEN'T HAD
A CHANCE TO COMPETE IN ANYTHING

15:23.748 --> 15:25.141
SINCE I HAD TO DROP
OUT OF THE OLYMPICS.

15:25.272 --> 15:27.013
I MISS THE RUSH.

15:27.143 --> 15:29.015
I WANT TO EXPERIENCE THE
THRILL OF VICTORY AGAIN.

15:29.145 --> 15:30.886
-OR THE AGONY OF DEFEAT.

15:31.582 --> 15:32.583
-HEY, I DON'T CARE.

15:33.323 --> 15:35.108
I JUST WANT TO GET
OUT THERE AND COMPETE.

15:37.327 --> 15:38.415
-CAN I BE YOUR COACH?

15:38.546 --> 15:39.895
[LAUGHING]

15:51.428 --> 15:52.212
-AHOY, SKIPPER.

15:52.342 --> 15:53.343
-AHOY.

15:53.474 --> 15:54.954
-PERMISSION TO GO ON BOARD.

15:55.084 --> 15:56.346
-PERMISSION GRANTED.

15:57.478 --> 15:59.959
UM, WRONG BOAT.

16:18.586 --> 16:19.761
-THIS IS YOUR BOAT?

16:23.025 --> 16:25.506
-NO, NO, NO,
MY YACHT'S IN THE SHOP.

16:25.636 --> 16:27.377
I'M JUST BORROWING
THIS BOAT FOR THE DAY.

16:27.508 --> 16:29.423
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT
TOO DISAPPOINTED.

16:33.340 --> 16:34.515
WELCOME ABOARD.

16:37.866 --> 16:38.736
WATCH YOUR HEAD.

16:38.867 --> 16:39.955
-OK.
-ALL RIGHT.

16:40.608 --> 16:41.739
OK.

16:42.784 --> 16:44.264
HEY DO ME A FAVOR, WOULD
YOU GRAB THE BOWLINE FOR ME?

16:44.394 --> 16:46.048
-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

16:46.179 --> 16:48.094
-I JUST NEED
A HAND CASTING OFF.

16:48.920 --> 16:50.400
-WELL, I THOUGHT
THAT FOR $5,000,

16:50.531 --> 16:52.533
I COULD JUST SIT BACK
AND ENJOY THE RIDE.

16:53.229 --> 16:54.578
-OKAY.

16:56.493 --> 16:57.538
-OR MAYBE WE SHOULD JUST
FORGET THE WHOLE THING

16:57.668 --> 16:59.235
AND JUST GET A MOTEL ROOM?

17:02.760 --> 17:04.196
-[CHUCKLES]

17:04.327 --> 17:05.415
-JUST A THOUGHT.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.353
SO, DO YOU DO THIS OFTEN?

17:30.484 --> 17:31.659
-SAIL?

17:32.573 --> 17:34.836
-NO, SELL YOURSELF
TO THE HIGHEST BIDDER?

17:36.272 --> 17:37.969
-NO, ACTUALLY THIS
IS MY FIRST TIME.

17:40.885 --> 17:43.192
-WELL, THEY SAY YOU NEVER
FORGET YOUR FIRST TIME.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.111
[LAUGHS]

18:12.482 --> 18:14.093
CAN'T YOU GET ANY CLOSER?

18:14.223 --> 18:17.400
-NO, WE'D GET GROUND
ON THOSE ROCKS UP THERE.

18:29.891 --> 18:31.458
ALL RIGHT, I'M
GONNA DROP ANCHOR.

18:32.415 --> 18:34.025
-ALICIA: YOU'RE SO NAUTICAL.

18:34.156 --> 18:35.331
-WHAT?

18:42.077 --> 18:43.122
-SEE YOU ON THE BEACH.

18:48.083 --> 18:50.041
DON'T FORGET MY BAG.

18:54.133 --> 18:55.308
-OKAY.

19:01.836 --> 19:02.706
OKAY.

19:15.066 --> 19:16.546
-MAN: GOOD JOB.
KEEP YOUR HEAD UP,

19:16.677 --> 19:17.678
KEEP YOUR HEAD UP.

19:18.287 --> 19:19.984
-ALL RIGHT, NICE PASS.

19:20.115 --> 19:21.595
-NOW, WHEN YOU TRANSITION,
YOU GOTTA GIVE A DROP PASS.

19:21.725 --> 19:22.509
-WHOO!

19:22.639 --> 19:23.510
-GOOD JOB!

19:23.640 --> 19:25.120
HERE YOU GO.

19:26.469 --> 19:28.123
-WOW, THIS IS A FESTIVAL.

19:29.994 --> 19:31.300
-CAROLINE: AH, HAAGEN DAAS.

19:31.431 --> 19:32.823
-WHOA, CAROLINE, NO,
NO, NO, NO, LATER.

19:32.954 --> 19:33.737
A BIG ONE. LATER.

19:33.868 --> 19:34.912
[LAUGHING]

19:36.305 --> 19:38.307
OH, CODY! WHOO!

19:39.134 --> 19:40.440
-HEY!

19:40.570 --> 19:41.310
-HI, HANDSOME!
-STEPHANIE: LOOKIN' GOOD!

19:48.796 --> 19:49.971
-MAN: WAY TO GO, MAN.

19:50.798 --> 19:51.668
LET'S GO.

19:56.673 --> 19:58.414
-HEY, THAT LOOKS LIKE FUN.

19:58.545 --> 19:59.763
STEPH, WHY DON'T
YOU GIVE IT A TRY?

19:59.894 --> 20:01.287
-ME? WHY DON'T YOU TRY IT?

20:01.417 --> 20:02.723
-ARE YOU NUTS? I JUST
GOT MY NAILS DONE.

20:02.853 --> 20:04.594
-OH, PLEASE, THAT'S
A POOR EXCUSE.

20:04.725 --> 20:05.856
HERE, TRY IT. DON'T BE A WIMP.

20:06.379 --> 20:08.076
-ALL RIGHT, WHAT DO I DO?

20:08.207 --> 20:09.991
-TAKE THIS STICK AND WHACK
THE BALL AS HARD AS YOU CAN.

20:10.644 --> 20:11.993
-SOUNDS VERY EASY.

20:18.347 --> 20:20.088
[LAUGHING]

20:21.263 --> 20:23.047
REALLY? YOU COULD DO BETTER?

20:23.178 --> 20:24.397
-YES, I COULD.

20:26.181 --> 20:27.530
-CAN I TRY AGAIN, PLEASE?

20:27.661 --> 20:28.618
-BY ALL MEANS.

20:30.794 --> 20:32.231
-YOU'RE HOLDING
THE STICK WRONG.

20:34.320 --> 20:35.625
TRY IT LIKE THIS.

20:38.411 --> 20:39.368
THAT'S PERFECT.

20:39.499 --> 20:41.065
NOW KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN,

20:41.196 --> 20:42.980
AND YOUR EYES ON THE BALL,

20:43.111 --> 20:44.417
SWING HARD.

20:46.767 --> 20:47.942
NICE SHOT.

20:49.726 --> 20:52.338
YOU KNOW, IF YOU'RE INTERESTED
IN LEARNING HOW TO PLAY,

20:53.208 --> 20:54.165
I GIVE PRIVATE LESSONS.

20:54.296 --> 20:55.645
-I DON'T THINK SO, PAL.

20:56.429 --> 20:58.300
-WELL, THE OFFER STILL STANDS.

21:03.653 --> 21:04.698
-WHO WAS THAT?

21:04.828 --> 21:06.613
-VINCENT MCHALE.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.789
HE WAS SUPPOSED TO PLAY IN THE
NHL, BUT IT NEVER HAPPENED.

21:08.919 --> 21:10.486
-I THINK HE'S CUTE.

21:11.095 --> 21:13.794
-CAROLINE, THAT'S A GUY
YOU SHOULD STAY AWAY FROM.

21:13.924 --> 21:15.143
-OR KNOCK ON HIS BUTT.

21:16.971 --> 21:18.842
-HEY, CODY, GOOD LUCK.
-CODY: THANKS.

21:18.973 --> 21:20.279
-WE'LL BE WATCHIN'.

21:21.149 --> 21:22.368
ALL RIGHT, LET ME TRY THAT.

21:22.498 --> 21:23.891
-FINE. FINE.

21:24.587 --> 21:26.285
-I'M A NATURAL. I CAN FEEL IT.

21:29.592 --> 21:31.290
WHOO! [LAUGHING]

21:31.420 --> 21:33.335
-THAT WAS BEGINNER'S LUCK.
-YEAH, RIGHT.

21:33.466 --> 21:37.034
[SLOW INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

21:52.223 --> 21:53.442
-BONJOUR, MADAME.

21:54.574 --> 21:56.315
LUNCH IS SERVED.

21:57.838 --> 21:59.143
A LITTLE WHITE VINO.

22:00.928 --> 22:02.016
NAPKIN.

22:03.147 --> 22:06.107
AND FOR THE FIRST
COURSE WE HAVE CHEESE.

22:11.373 --> 22:12.374
-UGH.

22:14.158 --> 22:15.943
THAT CHEESE TASTES
WORSE THAN IT SMELLS.

22:17.988 --> 22:19.555
I HOPE THERE'S SOMETHING
HERE THAT'S EDIBLE.

22:19.686 --> 22:21.383
-I'M SURE WE CAN
FIND SOMETHING.

22:21.514 --> 22:22.732
HAM?

22:25.692 --> 22:27.911
-UGH, NOT WHEN
IT'S FATTY LIKE THAT.

22:28.042 --> 22:29.304
[SOFTLY LAUGHING]

22:29.913 --> 22:31.872
-AH-HA, FRESH TURKEY.

22:32.786 --> 22:34.048
-I'M ALLERGIC TO FOWL.

22:34.178 --> 22:37.094
-[LAUGHS] OF COURSE YOU ARE.

22:38.748 --> 22:40.446
LITTLE PASTA SALAD?

22:42.839 --> 22:44.363
-THAT LOOKS ABOUT A WEEK OLD.

22:46.843 --> 22:47.931
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

22:48.062 --> 22:49.280
I'M WATCHING MY WEIGHT.

22:53.154 --> 22:54.590
-[MAKING SOUNDS OF PAIN]

22:56.200 --> 22:57.245
-WHAT?

22:57.898 --> 22:59.116
-BRAIN FREEZE.

23:01.728 --> 23:04.861
YOU SERVE WHITE WINE
CHILLED, NOT FROZEN.

23:05.862 --> 23:07.603
NOW, I'M PROBABLY
GONNA HAVE A HEADACHE
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

23:07.734 --> 23:09.692
-YOU KNOW, MAYBE
WE SHOULD GO BACK,

23:09.823 --> 23:12.216
BECAUSE NOTHING I DO
IS GOOD ENOUGH FOR YOU,

23:12.347 --> 23:14.175
SO I DON'T WANT TO WASTE
ANY MORE OF YOUR TIME,

23:14.305 --> 23:15.306
OR MINE, HUH?

23:16.917 --> 23:19.354
-JEEZ, WHAT ARE YOU
GETTING SO UPSET ABOUT?

23:19.485 --> 23:20.964
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU COOKED IT.

23:22.009 --> 23:23.532
YOU'VE GOT
LOUSY TASTE IN DELIS.

23:23.663 --> 23:24.838
I CAN OVERLOOK THAT.

23:25.882 --> 23:28.189
I'M SURE YOU COMPENSATE
IN OTHER AREAS.

23:28.319 --> 23:29.973
-I THINK WE SHOULD HEAD BACK.

23:31.192 --> 23:32.541
BESIDES,
THE WIND IS PICKING UP,

23:32.672 --> 23:33.890
AND THAT'S NOT A GOOD SIGN.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.197
-WELL, WE JUST GOT HERE.

23:36.327 --> 23:37.807
I THOUGHT THIS WAS GOING
TO BE AN ADVENTURE.

23:37.938 --> 23:39.766
I MEAN, AREN'T THERE
SOME CAVES, OR GROTTOES,

23:39.896 --> 23:40.810
WE CAN EXPLORE?

23:41.507 --> 23:42.856
-NO, NO!

23:42.986 --> 23:44.684
THERE ARE NO CAVES.

23:44.814 --> 23:46.076
THERE ARE NO GROTTOES,

23:46.207 --> 23:47.643
AND I THINK WE SHOULD
JUST HEAD BACK,

23:47.774 --> 23:48.992
SO START PACKIN' UP!

23:49.863 --> 23:52.300
-ALICIA: NOT UNTIL
WE'VE HAD OUR ADVENTURE.

23:53.214 --> 23:54.650
-GROTTOES AND ADVENTURES,

23:54.781 --> 23:56.435
HOW THE HELL DID I GET
TALKED INTO THIS ONE?

24:00.874 --> 24:01.875
OH, NO!

24:02.005 --> 24:03.006
-WHAT'S WRONG?

24:08.011 --> 24:10.187
OH, MY GOD.

24:10.840 --> 24:12.363
MITCH, GET THAT BOAT!

24:15.497 --> 24:17.020
WELL, UH...

24:22.330 --> 24:23.940
GET OUT THERE!

24:26.726 --> 24:30.860
[DRAMATIC INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

24:42.176 --> 24:43.612
WHY ARE YOU STOPPING?

24:45.440 --> 24:47.094
-MITCH: IT'S CAUGHT
IN THE CURRENT.

24:47.224 --> 24:48.182
-ALICIA: WHAT?

24:49.009 --> 24:50.227
-MITCH: IT'S GONE.

24:58.627 --> 25:00.281
-ALICIA: I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

25:03.240 --> 25:04.328
HOW?

25:04.459 --> 25:06.287
HOW COULD YOU
LET THIS HAPPEN?

25:07.941 --> 25:10.378
-THE ANCHOR DIDN'T SET
PROPERLY, I'M SORRY.

25:10.509 --> 25:12.336
-YOU'RE SORRY?
-YEAH, I'M SORRY.

25:12.467 --> 25:14.121
OH, YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND
THE WORDS, I'M SORRY,

25:14.251 --> 25:16.515
BECAUSE YOU'VE NEVER
MADE A MISTAKE, HAVE YOU?

25:16.645 --> 25:18.038
-NO, I HAVE NEVER
GOTTEN ANYONE STRANDED

25:18.168 --> 25:19.387
ON A DESERT ISLAND BEFORE.

25:19.518 --> 25:21.171
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

25:21.302 --> 25:22.521
-I WASN'T THINKING.

25:22.651 --> 25:23.870
I WAS DISTRACTED.

25:24.958 --> 25:27.526
-OH, SO NOW THIS IS MY FAULT,

25:27.656 --> 25:30.050
BECAUSE I WENT FOR A
SWIM IN THE NUDE? PLEASE!

25:30.180 --> 25:32.748
-OKAY, OKAY, LOOK, LET'S JUST
START OVER, ALL RIGHT?

25:32.879 --> 25:33.880
I AM SORRY.

25:34.881 --> 25:36.230
WE'RE NOT STRANDED.

25:36.360 --> 25:37.753
SOMEBODY'S GONNA
FIND US ON THE BEACH,

25:37.884 --> 25:39.668
OR THEY'RE GONNA FIND
THE BOAT, ALL RIGHT?

25:39.799 --> 25:42.410
LOOK, WORSE COMES TO WORST,
WE GOTTA SPEND THE NIGHT HERE.

25:43.063 --> 25:44.412
-SPEND THE NIGHT?

25:45.413 --> 25:46.414
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

25:46.545 --> 25:48.329
SEE, I DON'T SLEEP OUTSIDE.

25:48.459 --> 25:50.026
I NEED A VERY FIRM MATTRESS,

25:50.157 --> 25:51.332
OR I WILL WAKE UP
WITH A STIFF NECK.

25:52.420 --> 25:54.640
BESIDES, I HAVE DINNER
RESERVATIONS AT SPAGO TONIGHT,

25:54.770 --> 25:56.250
AND IF I DON'T SHOW UP,
I WILL NEVER GET
A GOOD TABLE AGAIN.

25:56.380 --> 25:58.600
-OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.

25:58.731 --> 26:01.908
WELL, THEN WE BETTER
GATHER SOME PALM FRONDS,

26:02.038 --> 26:03.997
BECAUSE WE NEED
TO BUILD A SIGNAL FIRE.

26:04.127 --> 26:05.389
I THINK YOU SHOULD HELP ME.

26:05.520 --> 26:07.435
THE DRIER ONES
BURN MUCH BETTER!

26:07.566 --> 26:10.090
-I'M NOT TOUCHING
ANY PALM FRONDS.

26:10.220 --> 26:12.266
THEY HAVE THESE LITTLE PRICKLY
THINGS ALL ALONG THE EDGES,

26:12.396 --> 26:14.268
AND I HAVE VERY SENSITIVE SKIN.

26:14.398 --> 26:16.662
BESIDES, YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE
FOR GETTING US INTO THIS MESS,

26:16.792 --> 26:18.228
WHY SHOULD I HAVE
TO BAIL YOU OUT?

26:18.359 --> 26:20.622
YOU GATHER
YOUR OWN PALM FRONDS.

26:22.015 --> 26:24.191
-I DON'T THINK WE'RE GONNA
MAKE IT THROUGH THE NIGHT.

26:28.064 --> 26:29.718
-MALE ANNOUNCER: WE'VE GOT
LESS THAN A MINUTE TO PLAY

26:29.849 --> 26:31.372
IN THIS SEMIFINAL GAME.

26:31.502 --> 26:33.156
HUNTINGTON BEACH STILL
LEADING WILL ROGERS BY ONE.

26:35.419 --> 26:36.986
-MAN: SHOOT IT,
SHOOT IT, SHOOT IT!

26:37.683 --> 26:38.727
-ANNOUNCER: FIVE
SECONDS TO PLAY NOW.

26:38.858 --> 26:40.163
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

26:40.294 --> 26:42.209
GOAL BY CODY MADISON!

26:42.339 --> 26:44.907
JUST AS TIME RUNS
OUT IN REGULATION.

26:45.038 --> 26:46.561
WOW! WHAT A FINISH.

26:46.692 --> 26:48.302
WE'RE GONNA LET THE
PLAYERS CATCH THEIR BREATH

26:48.432 --> 26:50.521
BEFORE WE GO INTO OVERTIME.

26:50.652 --> 26:52.654
MEANWHILE ON COURT TWO,

26:52.785 --> 26:55.135
DOCKWEILER'S ABOUT TO WIN
THEIR SEMIFINAL MATCH
AGAINST LAGUNA.

26:57.137 --> 26:59.487
NUMBER 16 HAS GOT THE
BALL, MOVING UP THE SLOT.

26:59.618 --> 27:01.837
HE'S GOT VINCENT MCHALE,

27:01.968 --> 27:02.969
GONNA HIT HIM
FOR THE HAT TRICK.

27:03.099 --> 27:04.492
HE DOES, HE SHOOTS, HE SCORES!

27:04.623 --> 27:07.234
VINCENT MCHALE GETS HIS
THIRD GOAL OF THE GAME.

27:07.364 --> 27:09.410
BOY, IS THAT KID
SOMETHIN' OR WHAT?

27:10.280 --> 27:12.500
DOCKWEILER ADVANCES
TO THE FINALS,

27:12.631 --> 27:13.849
WHERE THEY'LL MEET THE WINNER

27:13.980 --> 27:16.025
OF THE WILL
ROGERS-HUNTINGTON GAME.

27:16.156 --> 27:17.897
-LOOKS LIKE WE GET
THE DOCKWEILERS IN FINALS.

27:18.027 --> 27:19.463
-WE GOTTA WIN THIS ONE FIRST.

27:19.594 --> 27:20.639
COME ON, LET'S DO IT.

27:20.769 --> 27:22.553
-MEN: LET'S GO!

27:23.293 --> 27:24.773
-ANNOUNCER:
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

27:24.904 --> 27:27.428
WE'RE ABOUT TO BEGIN
SUDDEN DEATH OVERTIME.

27:27.558 --> 27:29.343
THE FIRST TEAM TO SCORE, WINS.

27:29.473 --> 27:31.040
AND IF NO ONE WINS IN THREE
MINUTES, WE GO TO A SHOOT OUT.

27:34.304 --> 27:38.657
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

27:40.746 --> 27:42.182
-MAN: WITH YOU,
WITH YOU, WITH YOU.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.328
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

27:58.459 --> 28:00.026
-ANNOUNCER:
THAT'S MADISON AGAIN

28:00.156 --> 28:02.593
SCORING THE GAME
WINNER FOR WILL ROGERS.

28:02.724 --> 28:06.380
[AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND SCREAMING]

28:22.309 --> 28:24.572
-NOT HAVING MUCH LUCK, ARE YOU?

28:25.399 --> 28:27.096
-IT RAINED LAST NIGHT.

28:27.227 --> 28:29.185
EVERYTHING IS STILL
A LITTLE DAMP.

28:33.537 --> 28:37.019
-AREN'T THERE SOME HIKERS,
OR SOME CAMPERS SOMEWHERE?

28:37.672 --> 28:41.197
SOMEONE WHO CAN HELP US GET
OFF THIS GODFORSAKEN SAND PILE?

28:41.328 --> 28:44.374
-MAYBE, ON THE OTHER
END OF THE ISLAND.

28:45.419 --> 28:47.508
YOU'RE WELCOME TO GO LOOK
FOR THEM ANYTIME YOU WANT.

28:47.638 --> 28:49.205
IT'S ONLY ABOUT
FIVE MILES ACROSS.

28:49.336 --> 28:51.730
YOU SHOULD BE BACK BY NIGHTFALL.

28:56.256 --> 28:58.867
OH, JUST SO YOU KNOW, THAT'S
OUR LAST BOTTLE OF WATER.

29:00.434 --> 29:01.217
-WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY ANYTHING?

29:01.348 --> 29:02.349
-WHY DIDN'T YOU ASK?

29:02.479 --> 29:03.437
-I WAS THIRSTY.

29:03.567 --> 29:04.786
-NO, YOU'RE SELFISH.

29:04.917 --> 29:06.353
ALL YOU DO IS THINK
ABOUT YOURSELF.

29:08.224 --> 29:10.923
-BOY, THIS IS REALLY
TURNING INTO A DREAM DATE.

29:13.621 --> 29:15.928
I GUESS I SHOULD GO FORAGING
NOW FOR NUTS AND BERRIES,

29:16.058 --> 29:19.366
OTHERWISE WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
EAT YOUR GOURMET PICNIC LUNCH.

29:24.545 --> 29:26.503
MITCH, THERE'S A BOAT!

29:27.374 --> 29:28.984
OVER HERE!

29:29.115 --> 29:30.594
OVER HERE!

29:30.725 --> 29:32.074
HURRY UP, GET THAT FIRE GOING.

29:32.205 --> 29:33.902
-IT WOULD'VE BEEN GOING BY NOW

29:34.033 --> 29:35.556
IF YOU'D GOTTEN OFF
YOUR DUFF AND HELPED.

29:35.686 --> 29:37.253
-OH, ONCE AGAIN IT'S MY FAULT.

29:37.384 --> 29:38.689
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA TAKE
RESPONSIBILITY FOR YOUR ACTIONS?

29:40.169 --> 29:42.737
MAYDAY! MAYDAY!

29:42.868 --> 29:44.826
COME ON, IT'S GONNA BE GONE.

29:44.957 --> 29:46.045
HURRY!

29:46.872 --> 29:48.177
WHERE'S THE SMOKE?

29:55.010 --> 29:56.098
IT'S GONE.

29:58.100 --> 30:00.189
HOW COULD YOU BE SO INEPT?

30:01.060 --> 30:02.017
[GRUNTS]

30:03.758 --> 30:05.847
THIS IS IT. I'VE HAD IT.

30:06.369 --> 30:07.240
[GRUNTS]

30:12.245 --> 30:14.769
GREAT,
WAY TO GO, MR. LIFESAVER.

30:17.728 --> 30:20.862
-ANNOUNCER: LADIES AND
GENTLEMEN, IT'S FACE OFF TIME

30:20.993 --> 30:23.778
FOR THE NHL BREAKOUT
CHAMPIONSHIP GAME.

30:23.909 --> 30:24.735
-WHAT IS THIS?

30:24.866 --> 30:26.215
-IT'S MY ADDRESS.

30:26.868 --> 30:29.088
WE'LL BE CELEBRATING OUR
VICTORY AFTER THE GAME TODAY.

30:29.653 --> 30:30.567
YOU SHOULD COME BY.

30:33.266 --> 30:34.571
YOU CAN COME TOO, IF YOU WANT.

30:37.444 --> 30:38.662
-IN YOUR DREAMS.

30:38.793 --> 30:40.708
-HEY! I STILL THINK HE'S CUTE.

30:40.839 --> 30:42.971
-HE'S CUTE, BUT HE'S MEAN.

30:45.974 --> 30:47.149
-LET'S HAVE A GOOD GAME.

30:47.846 --> 30:48.977
GOOD LUCK, GUYS.

30:51.719 --> 30:53.025
[AUDIENCE CHEERS AND CLAPS]

30:53.155 --> 30:55.070
-GO, CODY!

30:55.723 --> 30:57.072
-GOALIE!

30:58.117 --> 30:59.770
GOALIE!

31:00.989 --> 31:02.077
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:04.732 --> 31:08.605
[DRAMATIC INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

31:18.093 --> 31:18.964
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:19.094 --> 31:20.530
-ANNOUNCER: HE SCORES!

31:20.661 --> 31:22.228
AND WILL ROGERS TAKES
A ONE-NOTHING LEAD.

31:22.358 --> 31:23.664
-MAN: YEAH!
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:27.450 --> 31:28.669
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:32.673 --> 31:34.893
-MAN 1: RIGHT SIDE,
RIGHT SIDE, RIGHT SIDE.

31:42.988 --> 31:44.119
-MAN 2: COME ON!

32:07.273 --> 32:08.839
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

32:08.970 --> 32:10.580
-ANNOUNCER: VINCENT MCHALE
SCORES FOR DOCKWEILER.

32:10.711 --> 32:12.104
WE'RE ALL TIED UP.

32:12.234 --> 32:15.455
[DRAMATIC INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

32:51.795 --> 32:52.709
-WHAT?

32:53.972 --> 32:54.973
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

32:55.103 --> 32:56.583
[AUDIENCE BOOS]

33:00.065 --> 33:02.197
[AUDIENCE CHEERS]

33:08.899 --> 33:10.292
[AUDIENCE BOOS]

33:37.450 --> 33:38.407
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

33:38.538 --> 33:40.148
[CROWD BOOS]

33:40.279 --> 33:41.976
-ANNOUNCER:
VINCENT MCHALE AGAIN.

33:42.107 --> 33:44.500
THE SECOND OF THE GAME, AND
DOCKWEILER TAKES THE LEAD.

33:45.327 --> 33:46.241
-YEAH!

34:09.960 --> 34:12.005
[WHISTLE BLOWS]
[CROWD CHEERS]

34:12.137 --> 34:14.052
-ANNOUNCER:
THAT GOAL BY CODY MADISON

34:14.181 --> 34:16.489
TIES US UP AT TWO, FOLKS,
WITH JUST 30 SECONDS

34:16.619 --> 34:18.143
REMAINING ON THE CLOCK.

34:19.666 --> 34:20.841
TWENTY SECONDS.

34:28.588 --> 34:30.155
TEN SECONDS.

34:35.420 --> 34:36.900
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

34:37.771 --> 34:39.077
[CROWD BOOS]

34:39.206 --> 34:41.731
-THAT'S NUMBER
FOUR, PENALTY SHOT.

34:41.862 --> 34:43.777
-GIVE ME A TIMEOUT.

34:43.907 --> 34:45.257
-REFEREE: TIMEOUT, RED.

34:46.780 --> 34:48.563
-ANNOUNCER: NOW, HOLD
ON A SECOND, FOLKS.

34:48.695 --> 34:51.219
LOOKS LIKE WE GOT A PENALTY
CALL JUST AS TIME EXPIRED.

34:51.350 --> 34:52.742
-CODY, IT'S YOUR SHOT, MAN.

34:53.569 --> 34:54.788
-MY PLEASURE.

34:54.918 --> 34:56.181
-LET'S SEE WHAT
YOU GOT, BEACH BOY.

35:00.794 --> 35:03.971
-ANNOUNCER: IT'S MADISON VS.
MCHALE FOR THE CHAMPIONSHIP.

35:04.667 --> 35:05.886
MADISON SETS UP.

35:06.016 --> 35:07.757
-COME ON, CODY! WHOO!

35:08.454 --> 35:09.672
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

35:09.803 --> 35:10.804
-ANNOUNCER:
THERE'S THE WHISTLE.

35:10.934 --> 35:14.460
[DRAMATIC, INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

35:16.766 --> 35:18.203
MADISON'S DRIVING.

35:18.333 --> 35:20.118
MCHALE COMES OUT OF
HIS CREASE TO MEET HIM.

35:21.119 --> 35:22.511
HE SNEAKS LEFT, HE SHOOTS,

35:22.642 --> 35:24.034
HE SCORES!

35:24.165 --> 35:26.515
AND CODY MADISON WINS IT
FOR WILL ROGERS!

35:36.264 --> 35:37.265
-GOOD JOB! LET'S DO IT.

35:37.396 --> 35:39.137
-IN YOUR FACE! WHOO-HOO!

35:39.267 --> 35:41.269
LET'S GO SHAKE THEIR HANDS.
COME ON, LET'S GO.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.228
-ANNOUNCER: WELL, LET'S
HAVE A BIG ROUND OF APPLAUSE
FOR BOTH TEAMS.

35:43.358 --> 35:45.621
-GOOD GAME, MAN.
-GOOD GAME.

35:45.752 --> 35:48.189
-ALL RIGHT, GOOD GAME.
-GOOD GAME.

35:48.320 --> 35:49.364
-HEY, MAN, NICE GAME.

35:49.495 --> 35:50.496
-LUCKY SHOT.

35:52.237 --> 35:53.238
-STUPID FOUL.

35:54.935 --> 35:56.502
-COME HERE, YOU BIG STUD.

35:59.548 --> 36:00.636
YUCK!

36:00.767 --> 36:01.811
-YES.
-CONGRATULATIONS.

36:03.509 --> 36:04.423
-THANKS.

36:04.553 --> 36:05.728
-YOU WERE FANTASTIC.

36:06.381 --> 36:08.078
-IT'S NOT HE OLYMPICS,
BUT...

36:09.036 --> 36:09.993
I'LL TAKE IT.

36:11.995 --> 36:13.519
HIGH FIVE!

36:13.649 --> 36:14.781
-WHOO!

36:26.184 --> 36:27.620
-IT'S GONNA BE DARK SOON.

36:28.186 --> 36:29.187
-YEP.

36:32.973 --> 36:35.193
-WHAT DO YOU THINK OUR
CHANCES OF GETTING RESCUED ARE?

36:37.020 --> 36:38.152
-DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

36:41.808 --> 36:43.288
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE RIGHT.

36:43.418 --> 36:45.899
THIS PASTA STINKS.

36:49.511 --> 36:51.818
-WELL, THAT PEACH DOESN'T
LOOK TOO BADLY BRUISED.

36:51.948 --> 36:53.602
-OH, RIGHT AGAIN.

36:58.955 --> 37:00.218
-YOU'RE NOT GONNA
GIVE ME ANYTHING?

37:02.611 --> 37:04.222
YOU PREFER I STARVE?

37:07.399 --> 37:10.184
OK, FINE, DON'T
GIVE ME ANY FOOD.

37:10.837 --> 37:12.142
DON'T BE A GENTLEMAN.

37:15.624 --> 37:16.930
YOU KNOW, IT'S GONNA
GET PRETTY CHILLY

37:17.060 --> 37:18.018
WHEN THE SUN GOES DOWN.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.412
CAN I AT LEAST WEAR
YOUR WINDBREAKER?

37:22.979 --> 37:24.677
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO? BEG?

37:25.286 --> 37:26.809
TURN BLUE IN THE FACE?

37:27.462 --> 37:28.942
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE BEING SO PETTY.

37:31.292 --> 37:33.729
OR MAYBE THE KIND OF MAN THAT
LIKES TO WATCH A WOMAN SUFFER.

37:34.600 --> 37:36.384
-LADY, I'M THE ONE
THAT'S BEEN SUFFERING

37:36.515 --> 37:38.038
LISTENING TO YOU ALL DAY.

37:41.259 --> 37:42.695
SHOE'S ON
THE OTHER FOOT NOW.

37:43.217 --> 37:44.610
BETTER GET USED TO IT.

37:48.614 --> 37:50.877
-OH, REALLY?
-MITCH: HEY, STOP IT.

37:51.007 --> 37:51.878
-MAYBE YOUR FOOD
WILL TASTE BETTER WITH
SAND ALL OVER IT.
-MITCH: STOP IT!

37:52.008 --> 37:52.922
-MAKE ME, YOU CONFIDENT--

37:53.053 --> 37:54.620
-STOP IT! STOP IT!

37:58.624 --> 38:00.103
-I KNEW IT WAS JUST
A MATTER OF TIME

38:00.234 --> 38:01.540
BEFORE YOU GOT PHYSICAL.

38:01.670 --> 38:03.368
-I HARDLY TOUCHED YOU.

38:03.498 --> 38:05.979
-I'LL HAVE YOU KNOW THAT I
INTEND TO ASK FOR A FULL REFUND

38:06.109 --> 38:07.328
AS SOON AS WE GET BACK.

38:07.459 --> 38:09.852
THAT'S IF WE EVER GET BACK.

38:13.291 --> 38:14.640
AND IF I DON'T GET TO EAT,

38:14.770 --> 38:16.032
THEN NOBODY GETS TO EAT.

38:16.163 --> 38:18.426
-HEY, HEY, HEY,
DON'T, DON'T DO THAT!

38:18.948 --> 38:20.167
HEY, HEY, COME HERE,
COME HERE, DON'T!

38:20.298 --> 38:21.951
COME HERE, COME HERE!

38:23.649 --> 38:26.304
STOP IT! STOP IT!

38:54.854 --> 38:57.073
[HELICOPTER LOUDLY APPROACHES]

38:59.337 --> 39:01.382
-OH, WHAT'S THAT NOISE?

39:01.513 --> 39:03.297
-WE'RE BEING RESCUED.

39:07.475 --> 39:10.217
-RESCUED?
AH, PUT OUT THE FIRE.

39:10.348 --> 39:11.305
-I AM.

39:19.052 --> 39:20.401
AH, IT'S THE COASTIES.

39:20.532 --> 39:22.229
THEY MUST'VE FOUND THE BOAT.

39:23.796 --> 39:25.537
-THEY HAVEN'T FOUND US YET.

39:35.808 --> 39:38.158
-WELL, LOOKS LIKE
YOU'LL MAKE IT IN TIME

39:38.288 --> 39:39.638
FOR YOUR DINNER
AT SPAGO'S AFTER ALL.

39:39.768 --> 39:41.117
-THANK GOD.

39:41.944 --> 39:43.903
-WOULD YOU LIKE SOME COMPANY?

39:44.512 --> 39:46.558
-AH, HOW SWEET OF YOU TO ASK,

39:47.123 --> 39:49.604
BUT I PROMISED MY FIANCE
IT'D JUST BE THE TWO OF US.

39:52.041 --> 39:53.173
-YOUR FIANCE?

39:54.740 --> 39:56.872
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU WERE ENGAGED?

39:57.830 --> 39:58.961
-WHY DIDN'T YOU ASK?

40:01.703 --> 40:02.704
[CAR HORN HONKS]

40:03.575 --> 40:04.750
OH, THERE HE IS NOW.

40:04.880 --> 40:08.623
-[LAUGHS] I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

40:11.104 --> 40:12.192
WHAT ABOUT US?

40:13.149 --> 40:14.934
-WE'LL ALWAYS HAVE ANACAPA.

40:17.545 --> 40:18.720
BYE, MITCH.

40:48.141 --> 40:50.535
-SO, YOU MUST'VE HAD
SOME KIND OF ADVENTURE.

40:53.102 --> 40:54.147
-NEWMIE,

40:55.365 --> 40:57.672
THIS COULD BE THE START
OF A BEAUTIFUL FRIENDSHIP.

40:58.804 --> 40:59.631
-WHAT?

41:10.772 --> 41:12.861
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
